                  </hi>. I live in West-street, Saffron-hill. I had the care of the prosecutor's factory—on the 30th of May, between five and sir o'clock in the morning, I missed some lead, and I told my wife to watch—I saw the prisoner, running with some lead—I took him, he got from me, and was stopped again—I took this lead off his shoulder—I have fitted it to the place.</p>
